Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

Togo has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Togo, see Return to the UK
Entry and borders
Land borders have been closed since 20 March and there are now no options for entering the country on flights although there are limited commercial options for departures.
Those who already arrived in in Togo from countries with a significant number of coronavirus cases will self-isolate for two weeks under medical supervision, and then for a further week after testing for coronavirus. Those with confirmed cases of coronavirus are being hospitalised in CHR Lome Commune hospital.
Local measures
A state of emergency was declared on 2 April for 3 months and there is a curfew from 8 pm to 6am. An anti-pandemic special force has been put in place to police the curfew.
Healthcare
Those with concerns about coronavirus should call the government hotline on +228 91674242 or +228 22222073. There is also a freephone information number on 111. For more up-to-date information, in French, about the situation in Togo check the government website.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
